default3.2
default 
default The method by which Road Worker Safety is managed across the Network is deserving of major reform. For years, a flawed system has evolved which accepts significant conflict of interest between the HA and its major contractors. The Road Worker Safety Forum
default (RoWSaF), chaired by the HA, involves major contractors in the decision making process even though safety concerns and commercial interests are inevitably open to conflict of interest. This potentially allows powerful commercial vested interests to exerci
defaultse considerable influence over any SME wishing to enter this lucrative market with a new innovative, HA-approved, safety-driven product.
default&#xa0;
default-
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultin my view, this possibly explains the problem of the acceptance of poor data in respect of ‘reportable’ incidents, wh
defaultich has meant that the true extent of “reportable” incidents has not been brought fully to the attention of Ministers and Parliament for many years. 
default&#xa0;
